SUMMARY:The Chicago Briefing: Strengthening Global Democracy in a Changin
 g World.
DESCRIPTION:You are invited to an engaging evening of conversation hosted
  by the Hamilton Lugar School of Global and International Studies in part
 nership with Freedom House:Defending Democracy\, Countering Authoritarian
 ism\, and the Future of U.S. Global Leadership  This timely discussion wi
 ll explore the state of global freedom\, the rise of authoritarian influe
 nce\, and Dearthe policy choices shaping democratic resilience. Together\
 , we will examine how governments\, institutions\, and civil society are 
 responding to democratic backsliding—and what effective leadership look
 s like in this pivotal moment.Featured SpeakersJamie Fly\, CEO\, Freedom 
 HouseDavid Bosco\, Interim Dean\, Hamilton Lugar SchoolLink to RSVP - htt
 ps://iu.co1.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_cINhMDNa6W9XPZc
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><span data-olk-copy-source="MessageBody">
 You are invited to an engaging evening of conversation hosted by the Hami
 lton Lugar School of Global and International Studies in partnership with
  Freedom House:<br /><br /><strong>Defending Democracy\, Countering Autho
 ritarianism\, and the Future of U.S. Global Leadership</strong><br /><br 
 />  This timely discussion will explore the state of global freedom\, the
  rise of authoritarian influence\, and Dearthe policy choices shaping dem
 ocratic resilience. Together\, we will examine how governments\, institut
 ions\, and civil society are responding to democratic backsliding—and w
 hat effective leadership looks like in this pivotal moment.</span></p><p>
