DESCRIPTION:The Diplomacy Lab is a practitioner-led partnership that allo
 ws the Hamilton Lugar School to provide direct analysis for the U.S. Depa
 rtment of State. This isn't just a research project—it's a chance to co
 nsult on urgent global challenges\, from climate security to digital free
 dom\, directly from Bloomington.  Join us on September 11 for a strategic
  briefing on the Spring 2027 cycle. We will move beyond the syllabus to s
 how you how to form a team\, align with faculty expertise\, and submit a 
 winning bid.What we will cover:The Matchmaking Strategy: Using our intern
 al interest lists to pair student technical skills with faculty subject-m
 atter expertise.    The Bidding Mechanics: A step-by-step guide to the pr
 oject menu and the requirements for faculty-led submissions.    The 3-Cre
 dit Standard: Why we are standardizing the Lab experience to ensure profe
 ssional parity and academic rigor.    Lessons Learned: A panel of HLS fac
 ulty and students will discuss their experiences managing previous teams 
 and project IDs.    Who should attend?Faculty looking to integrate practi
 tioner-led tradecraft into their research.    Students eager to build a p
 rofessional portfolio of "Day 1" assets.
